{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17535369","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17535369"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:55:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:55:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15342"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15342","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15342"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.07,0.77,0.01,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8033"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82121"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8033","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8033"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15342"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67317"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"133"},{"type":"tags","id":"181"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1674"},{"type":"tags","id":"1914"},{"type":"tags","id":"3696"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5254"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19513"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27987"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82121","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/82121"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old man presents with a two day history of fever, abdominal pain and diarrhoea. His medical history includes known alcohol-related chronic liver disease and hepatic encephalopathy. On examination his blood pressure is 108/65, pulse 92/min and temperature 37.0\u00b0C. He has a uniformly distended and tender abdomen with shifting dullness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn ascitic tap is performed and the fluid has a white cell count greater than 250 cells/mm\u00b3.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following antibiotics should be given immediately?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Amoxicillin","Azithromycin","Ceftriaxone","Oseltamivir","Rifampicin"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis clinical scenario describes spontaneous bacterial peritonitis (SBP) in a patient with chronic liver disease. The diagnosis is supported by the elevated ascitic fluid white cell count above 250 cells/mm\u00b3, along with typical symptoms including fever, abdominal pain, and encephalopathy. Without early treatment, the mortality risk is high.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECeftriaxone\u003C/strong\u003E, a third-generation cephalosporin, is the first-line empiric treatment for SBP due to its excellent coverage of common causative organisms and good penetration into ascitic fluid. \u003Cstrong\u003EOseltamivir\u003C/strong\u003E is an antiviral medication used for influenza. \u003Cstrong\u003EAzithromycin\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily used for respiratory tract infections. \u003Cstrong\u003ERifampicin\u003C/strong\u003E is used for tuberculosis treatment. \u003Cstrong\u003EAmoxicillin\u003C/strong\u003E alone would provide inadequate coverage for the typical organisms causing SBP.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Spontaneous bacterial peritonitis in cirrhosis requires immediate empiric third-generation cephalosporin therapy.","Clinical features of spontaneous bacterial peritonitis include fever, abdominal pain, encephalopathy and ascites with elevated white cell count.","Early antibiotic treatment significantly reduces mortality in spontaneous bacterial peritonitis."],"references":["Dever JB, Sheikh MY. Review article: spontaneous bacterial peritonitis--bacteriology, diagnosis, treatment, risk factors and prevention. Aliment Pharmacol Ther. 2015 Jun;41(11):1116-31. doi: 10.1111/apt.13172. Epub 2015 Mar 26. PMID: 25819304.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808","Edelson J, Basso JE, Rockey DC. Updated strategies in the management of acute variceal haemorrhage. Curr Opin Gastroenterol. 2021 May 1;37(3):167-172. doi: 10.1097/MOG.0000000000000723. PMID: 33769373; PMCID: PMC8691141"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67317"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15342"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67317","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/67317"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-28T11:27:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-28T11:28:23+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8033"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82121"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links